abstract: We will go by state delegate equivalents, as we have in the past.
snippet: We will go by state delegate equivalents, as we have in the past.
lead_paragraph: This year, the results of the Iowa caucuses will be reported differently. That could create confusion for readers, muddle the outcome and allow multiple candidates to claim victory.

abstract: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
snippet: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, the Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state Sunday trying to fire up voters and make one last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
headline_main: In Iowa, Anxiety and Unpredictability Clouds Caucus Finish

headline_main: The Donors Powering the Campaign of Bernie Sanders
byline_original: By K.K. Rebecca Lai, Josh Katz, Rachel Shorey, Thomas Kaplan and Derek Watkins

abstract: When Bernie Sanders addresses throngs of supporters who gather at his rallies, the divisions that plague the Democratic Party can feel far away. The Vermont senator speaks of building a “mutliracial, mutli-generational movement" that will cut through economic divides, catapult him into the White House and transform the nation.
snippet: When Bernie Sanders addresses throngs of supporters who gather at his rallies, the divisions that plague the Democratic Party can feel far away. The Vermont senator speaks of building a “mutliracial, mutli-generational movement" that will cut thro...
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — When Bernie Sanders addresses throngs of supporters who gather at his rallies, the divisions that plague the Democratic Party can feel far away. The Vermont senator speaks of building a “mutliracial, mutli-generational movement" that will cut through economic divides, catapult him into the White House and transform the nation.
headline_main: Sanders Calls for Unity, but His Supporters Have Other Ideas
headline_print_headline: Sanders Calls for Unity, but His Supporters Have Other Ideas

abstract: The specter of the divisive Democratic battles of 2016 cast a shadow over the final days of the 2020 contest for Iowa as several candidates questioned the ability of Bernie Sanders to unite the party.
snippet: The specter of the divisive Democratic battles of 2016 cast a shadow over the final days of the 2020 contest for Iowa as several candidates questioned the ability of Bernie Sanders to unite the party.
lead_paragraph: ANAMOSA, Iowa — The specter of the divisive Democratic battles of 2016 cast a shadow over the final days of the 2020 contest for Iowa, as several leading presidential candidates questioned the ability of Senator Bernie Sanders to unite the party as its nominee while the Sanders camp sparred with allies of Hillary Clinton, his rival in the race four years ago.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Amid the campaigning and the schmoozing, the baby-kissing and hand-shaking, the political world prepared for a big arrival in Iowa on Saturday night.
headline_main: The last major poll of the Iowa caucuses comes out tonight.

abstract: An undecided voter told the former vice president that she hadn’t made up her mind, and asked what he would say to someone like her.
snippet: An undecided voter told the former vice president that she hadn’t made up her mind, and asked what he would say to someone like her.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS — As Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. neared the end of the rope line at his afternoon event here, shaking hands and taking pictures, he encountered Jaimee Warbasse, a hairstylist from Cedar Rapids who was still undecided.

abstract: With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.
snippet: With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-elec...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.
headline_main: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech
headline_print_headline: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech

abstract: U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren on Friday released a letter she sent to economist Judy Shelton, one of President Donald Trump's two planned nominees for seats on the Federal Reserve, raising "significant concerns" and posing a series of questions about her views.
snippet: U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren on Friday released a letter she sent to economist Judy Shelton, one of President Donald Trump's two planned nominees for seats on the Federal Reserve, raising "significant concerns" and posing a series of questions ab...
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — U.S. Senator Elizabeth Warren on Friday released a letter she sent to economist Judy Shelton, one of President Donald Trump's two planned nominees for seats on the Federal Reserve, raising "significant concerns" and posing a series of questions about her views.
headline_main: Warren Raises 'Significant Concerns' in Letter to Trump's Fed Pick Shelton
headline_print_headline: Warren Raises 'Significant Concerns' in Letter to Trump's Fed Pick Shelton
